chunks.overlap_context:
 autumn withering; flowering, fruiting, the ripening of the fruit, the rounding of the embryo—all occurs in accordance with the natural seasons, in harmony with heaven and earth. There is no need to rely on forced effort or laborious puffing, nor to exhaust oneself with external affairs.

Cease all clever artifice and contrived effort;
recognize the deathless method of another’s house.
In the pot, the life-sustaining wine is ever replenished;
in the tripod, the soul-returning nectar is gathered.
